The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Calcutta University Manuscript Resource Centre celebrated National Manuscript Day on Sunday at Ashutosh Hall, on the College Street campus. Centre coordinator Ratna Basu said the programme comprised a symposium, an interactive session among scholars and an exhibition of manuscripts. 

 Two pedestrians were injured after a cement-laden truck knocked them down on Kona Expressway on Sunday afternoon. The two were admitted to the district hospital. 

 Central trade unions will organise a convention against the UPA government?s Patent Act Amendment Ordinance on Tuesday. This was announced by Citu state secretary Debanjan Chakraborti on Sunday.

 The All India Minority Forum observed ?anti-terrorist day? on Sunday, the death anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi. A meeting on communal harmony was organised on Elliot Road. Speakers discussed the relevance of Gandhi?s principles in today?s world. 

 The civic body has written to the government seeking an extension of the waiver-of-interest scheme on outstanding property tax, officials said on Sunday. The scheme expires on Monday.

